Review: Part of being an adult is that sometimes you have to take an edible and go watch a musical for children

SMH I can’t believe we saw this just bc my Dad didn’t want to see Wonka there’s no way that movie isn’t better in like every single way. Fell asleep during the first half of this (it was boring) and then woke up just in time to be completely traumatized by the race scene. Nothing happened for the entire first hour and then right as it got interesting it just ended?

Movie: The Hunger Games: The Ballad of Songbirds & Snakes

Review: Can’t believe they let that fat ugly pig Anne Hathaway star in this…..

Impulse Netflix watch and had everything it needed to be good but sucked so hard Dad couldn’t even finish. Realized halfway thru that I think I’ve seen a Movies:Explained YouTube channel type video on this and kinda watched it through the lens of constantly half remembering some horrible YouTube film bro explaining every spoiler and Easter egg to my 15 year old self. Also it negates all the Alien vs Predator lore which is great lore.

This had truly Green Book level takes on trans issues which idk how to feel about… Waititi doesn’t really have the edge or the nuance to make something deeper tho so maybe it’s good this stayed so fluffy? But if u make a fun comedy movie about soccer I mean come on that is a movie Oliver will go see and at least like a little bit!
Sick and twisted! Last act had me yelling at the TV
